In [6]:
# Open, read, and plot post flood data
with rio.open(lidar_dtm_path_post_flood) as src:
    lidar_dtm_post_flood = src.read(1, masked=True)

print(lidar_dtm_pre_flood.min(), lidar_dtm_pre_flood.max())

# Find min, max elevation levels, so both pre- and post-flood plots share same scale
min_elevation = min(lidar_dtm_pre_flood.min(), lidar_dtm_post_flood.min())
max_elevation = max(lidar_dtm_pre_flood.max(), lidar_dtm_post_flood.max())
print(min_elevation, max_elevation)

              scale=False,
              cmap='seismic',
              title="Lidar Digital Terrain Model",
              vmax=10,
              vmin=-10)
